ram\": \"local official Elise Lavielle\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To mitigate that risk, lifeguards will assess visitors' swimming abilities before allowing independent access, while a decree issued in late June introduced fines for anyone swimming outside designated areas.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that risk\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1735}, {\"ngram\": \"lifeguards\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors' swimming abilities\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"independent access\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"a decree\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"late June\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1859}, {\"ngram\": \"fines\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1876}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"designated areas\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1921}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The promise to lift the swimming ban dates back to 1988, when then-mayor of Paris and future President Jacques Chirac first advocated for its reversal, about 65 years after the practice was banned in 1923.\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.52006673302638e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Chirac\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The promise\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming ban\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"then-mayor\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"its reversal\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"the practice\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One of my predecessors (Chirac), then mayor of Paris, dreamed of a Seine where everyone could swim,\\\" President Emmanuel Macron wrote on X, describing the move as the result of a \\\"collective effort\\\" and a moment of \\\"pride\\\" for France.\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.52006673302638e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2199, \"end\": 2204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.824284662638903e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999905388028413, \"rank\": 9.45377428350383e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my predecessors\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"Chirac\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2162}, {\"ngram\": \"mayor\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2219}, {\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"the move\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2290}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2304}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"collective effort\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2342}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"pride\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the Olympic Games, authorities invested approximately 1.4 billion euros ($1.6bn) to improve the Seine's water quality.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2474, \"end\": 2479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.824284662638903e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2395}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2408}, {\"ngram\": \"approximately 1.4 billion euros\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, work carried out upstream, including 2,000 new connections to the sewage system, promises even better water quality - with an unappetising catch.\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"2,000 new connections\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2568}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewage system\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2589}, {\"ngram\": \"even better water quality\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2625}, {\"ngram\": \"an unappetising catch\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On rainy days, the mid-19th-century Parisian sewage system often overflows, causing rain and wastewater to pour into the river.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2784, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rainy days\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2670}, {\"ngram\": \"the mid-19th-century Parisian sewage system\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2715}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2745}, {\"ngram\": \"wastewater\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2760}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 2783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Flags will inform bathers about pollution levels in the water every day, and if it rains, the sites will likely close the day after, said Paris city official Pierre Rabadan.\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2924, \"end\": 2929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.52006673302638e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2944, \"end\": 2958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre Rabadan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Flags\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2791}, {\"ngram\": \"bathers\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution levels\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2847}, {\"ngram\": \"the sites\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2885}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 2904, \"to\": 2911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The presence of the faecal bacteria Escherichia coli (E coli) and enterococci in the Seine will be assessed daily using live sensors and samples.\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 3106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2997, \"end\": 3013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3511667673678385e-24, \"text\": \"Escherichia coli\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\"}, {\"begin\": 3046, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.824284662638903e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The presence\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 2973}, {\"ngram\": \"the faecal bacteria\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2996}, {\"ngram\": \"enterococci\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3038}, {\"ngram\": \"live sensors\", \"from\": 3081, \"to\": 3093}, {\"ngram\": \"samples\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Varying weather conditions will be a critical factor.\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3161, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Varying weather conditions\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3134}, {\"ngram\": \"a critical factor\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmers may be in luck this year, though, with temperatures predicted to be drier than the record rainfall during the games, which had led to the cancellation of six of the 11 competitions held on the river.\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Swimmers\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3170}, {\"ngram\": \"luck\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"temperatures\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3222}, {\"ngram\": \"the record rainfall\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3269}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3286}, {\"ngram\": \"the cancellation\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3321}, {\"ngram\": \"the 11 competitions\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3351}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With record-breaking heat hitting Europe, including France's second warmest June since records began in 1900, authorities said they expect Parisians to embrace the relief of a refreshing swim.\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3424, \"end\": 3430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999905388028413, \"rank\": 9.45377428350383e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"type